        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 6:32PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 632 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Buford, or 14 miles east of Lancaster. This storm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Jefferson, Taxahaw, Pleasant Hill, High Point Fire Station, Kershaw
Correctional Institution, Tradesville, and Forty Acre Rock Preserve.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
central South Carolina.</instruction>
